Directorate General for Civil Aviation, a department of the Ministry of the Sea, Transport and Infrastructure, is competent for the overall civil aviation policy of the Republic of Croatia;
to establish national strategy on aviation development; the representation of the Republic of Croatia at international civil aviation organisations and organizations in the framework of the ECAA Agreement; to prepare and perform the negotiation and signature of bilateral and multilateral aviation agreements;
ensure the proper implementation of international aviation agreements concluded by Croatia; matters relating to the establishment and operation of scheduled air services ensuing from bilateral and multilateral aviation agreements; the adoption of secondary legislation as set out in the Air Traffic Act and the international agreements binding on the Republic of Croatia; to prepare draft proposals for laws in the field of civil aviation; to perform administrative monitoring of the Agency and Agency for investigation; high level decisions on Air Navigation matters except safety; to conduct proceedings on concession arrangements for aerodromes in accordance with the Act on Concessions and international agreements binding on the Republic of Croatia; to decide on the status of the airports and to appoint if necessary the independent slot allocation co-ordinator; to act upon appeals against the Agency administrative acts; performing proceedings on offences determined by the Air Traffic Act.

Fourel Aviation is an ecosystem of customizable off-the-shelf solutions for Business Aviation Companies.
1) Fourel CAMO – an integration with Camp, Traxxall, Rusada, Foreflight, and Garmin Flightbook, allows to digitize and automatically populate the LogBook data and reports, therefore significantly decreasing the volume of paperwork and probability of data loss or human-factor failures;
2) Fourel Flights – an integration with Avinode and Schedaero aligns the aircraft data with the flight management software, thus allowing to better track expenditures and calculate PNL for each booking, populate the reports and provide forecasts for new orders; 
3) Fourel CRM – a perfectly designed solution for managing the relationship with the clients, allowing to streamline and automate the invoicing, accept and track payments, simplify and organize communications with the clients, flight managers, brokers etc.;

